<h3>Do you service all LG dryer models and years?</h3>
<p>Yes, we repair everything from older DLGX models to the newest LG Signature and ThinQ smart dryers. Our technicians stay current on LG's latest designs and diagnostic procedures. We even handle discontinued models, though parts availability sometimes requires a day or two for sourcing.</p>
<h3>What are the most common LG dryer problems you encounter?</h3>
<p>Thermal fuse failures top the list, usually caused by restricted airflow. We also see frequent heating element burnouts, drum support roller wear, and door latch breakage. The newer smart models develop sensor issues and Wi-Fi connectivity problems that require specialized troubleshooting.</p>
<h3>Do you provide warranties on LG dryer repairs?</h3>
<p>Absolutely. All our repairs include warranty coverage on parts and labor. The specific terms depend on the component replaced, but if the same part fails during the warranty period, we'll fix it again at no charge. We stand behind our work completely.</p>
